snippet.textDisplay:
Loving Sanjit's voice as a fellow youth genZ and liked the inclusion of yaksagana artist here but ,if the set would have been made something alike it would have been better.Also, dont understand this , but why ONLY younger artists are lead vocals, and not our elderly artists too- want to see  MORE OF OUR ELDERLY ARTISTS as one from 50-60 above aged too- singing in our @CokeStudioBharat platform as they have so so much to offer in terms of art,its culture ,techniques and teach us a LOTTT❤ !! @coke studiobharat please search for our cultural preserves😅- the elderly experienced Indian classical/traditional singers from around India & world. Its really so nice and feels wholesome to see artists coming from all over India representing all our Indian cultures through such songs. Will love to hear more such from manipuri with maniuri dance representation too, naga culture, assamese with a Sattriya dancer on one side of the set maybe❤, so from malyalam,tamil, marathi, sikkim folk songs, jammu, Himachal's pahadi aura created set, malyali Goa's too and make the set like that too- AND PLEASE BE MINDFUL BY NOT STEREOTYPING THEM.
ALSO, PLEASE CREATE SONGS FOR ALL GENERATIONS, not only just for the youth.
